sentences: In 2014, Depper joined Ray LaMontagne's touring band; he was later recruited by Indie Rock pioneers Death Cab for Cutie during their 2015 world tour in support of their eighth album, Kintsugi.
In 2017, Depper released his first solo album, Emotional Freedom Technique, which was well-received by critics.
He attended the University of Oregon, where he studied computer and information science, graduating in 2002.
In 2014, Depper joined Ray LaMontagne's touring band; he was later recruited by Indie Rock pioneers Death Cab for Cutie during their 2015 world tour in support of their eighth album, Kintsugi.
Following the departure of member Chris Walla, Depper and fellow musician Zac Rae joined Death Cab as full-time members, receiving credits on the band's ninth album, Thank You for Today.
Depper grew up in Bend, Oregon and currently lives in Portland.
He then worked as a software engineer for several years before transitioning to working as a touring musician full-time.
